               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains a commentary on the book of Aphorisms attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="person_287984736">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Ar_454-item1">
                     <author key="person_4405945">
                        <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/4405945" type="aut">Ibn Abī Ṣādiq‏ابن أبي صادق</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7754">Commentary on Hippocratic Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7754">شرح فصول أبقراط</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="alt" key="work_7754">Sharḥ Fuṣūl Abuqrāṭ</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript in Manuscrits de la Fondation Georges et Mathilde Salem.</note>
                     <note>This is a lemmatically arranged commentary. The introduction begins on <locus>f. 1b</locus>; the beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk1: 2a (between f. 9 and f. 10 several folios are missing, so the copy lacks comm. on i. 12 to ii. 45); Bk3 (mislabeled "Bk2"); Bk4: 22a (between f. 43 and f. 44, a few folios are missing, so the copy lacks comm. on iv. 81-v.32); Bk6: 62b; Bk7: 101a. The copy is incomplete; quite a few folios are missing.</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/47128078" key="person_47128078">Sbath, Paul</author>
                           <date calendar="#Gregorian">1928-34</date>
                           <title>Bibliothèque de manuscrits Paul Sbath : catalogue. 3</title> p.96. <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/44576904" key="person_44576904">Río Sánchez, Francisco del</author>
                           <date calendar="#Gregorian">2008</date>
                           <title>Catalogue des manuscrits de la Fondation Georges et Mathilde Salem (Alep, Syrie)</title> p.253.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
